n class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Trials and Tribulations in SK</span><hr size=1> Heres my little story,<br>
<br>
One day i decided, while killing my millionth or so gnoll in South Karana, that i should probably find out what else there is to do in this little corner of Norrath.  Being that SK is about the largest zone in the game I was on the assumption that there were many things that could occupy my time.<br>
<br>
I recalled Aevatare saying something about a Certain Paladin quest and decided to get more info. So off to allakhazam site i go. And 'Lo and behold there it is. The Aegis of Life quest. A shield with massive Wisdom stats that can be worn on the back. &quot;OOOOHHHH NIIIIICE!!!&quot; i say to myself. And i proceed to devour all pertinant information to this task.<br>
<br>
Turns out that the MoB i need to kill has a placeholer. With a 3 hour 15 minute respawn time ACK! But never worry some kind soul has posted his way of catching the elusive Beastie who goes by the name Grimrot. So this is exasctly what i do. Head over to spawn area and see if PH'er is up. YIPPEE!! Its there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So Kill it, camp, log, wait three hours (Watch movie, Take out trash, Ponder the meaning of life) log back in and wait for pop. Oh well.....another PH'er. SOOOO...Kill, camp, llog etc. etc. <br>
<br>
This went on for about 3 days, on and off due to work and other such RL issues. During this time NOT ONCE did i find anyone else near my newfound home. And the death of many PH'ers continued. <br>
<br>
Just this eve when i decided to have one more go before beddie-bye, Log in and &quot;HEY whos that???&quot; Seems a Cleric and her Very Red to me SK buddy are in my spot. They most certainly dont seem to be hunting those lil' green skelly's. Doesnt take Sherlock to figure this one out.  So i think &quot;OH Well&quot; i'll just sit back and let them kill the next PH'er for me, laugh quietly to myself for thier misfortune, and log.<br>
<br>
But then.....You guessed it boys and girls....Good Ol' Grimmy is nice enough to show his face. And all i can do is cry on my keyboard screaming at the monitor &quot;HEY THATS MINE&quot; &quot;WWAAAAHHHHHH!!&quot;  While they rip him limb from limb. <br>
<br>
But such is life in EQ eh?<br>
Oh and sorry for the rambling I just needed a vent i guess. And monitor replacement gets costly<br>
<br>
Your Pally,<br>
Montag <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/udanase.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danase</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arrow of Light</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000080>(9/27/02 8:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Trials and Tribulations in SK</span><hr size=1> /hugs Montag<br>
